Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light red-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with Helios head symbol.
Curator's comments: Worn pencil, circled. Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 200, 1. Name Archokrates.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0878)
